results.name: Number of factorizations of n that are empty or whose factors have a common divisor > 1.
comment: First differs from A319786 at a(900) = 11, A319786(900) = 12.
A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798. Numbers whose prime indices have a common divisor > 1 are listed in A318978.
link: Gus Wiseman, Sequences counting and encoding certain classes of multisets
